"It's already been three years since then, huh? It
feels almost like it was just yesterday."\n<Yukine>
"You sound like an old lady♪"\n<Shuo>
"Hey... don't say things like that."\n<Yukine>

"I'm sorry. You're right, there's no way such a
cute old lady exists\I[84]"\n<Shuo>

"Geez... you've become quite the chatterbox,
haven't you, Sakura."\n<Yukine>

I've heard a lot from Sakura since then. That
Sakuragatsu is a divine being that descended from
the moon and resided in an ancient stone.

Unable to return to the moon, she slept alone in
the mountains for a long time. She met a young
girl and gained many emotions. And unable to
forget the warmth of people, she twisted her
divinity in solitude and fell.

All of this, Sakura, who inherited the memories
and powers, taught me bit by bit.

"But we were really lucky, weren't we? Even though
our divine status was completely different."\n<Yukine>

"Surely, Sakuragatsu-sama must have wanted warmth
too."\n<Shuo>

"She must have been so lonely that she even forgot
her own name... Sakuragatsu-sama..."\n<Yukine>

"But now we're together, so let's leave the gloomy
stories behind."\n<Shuo>

"It's about time for a walk, isn't it? Yukine
Onee-san."\n<Shuo>

"That's right, Sakura. The weather is nice today
as well, so shall we go for a walk?"\n<Shuo>
